    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn56.18:1.1",
          "pli": "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: ",
          "en": "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn56.18:1.2",
          "pli": "“‘vijjā, vijjā’ti, bhante, vuccati. ",
          "en": "“Sir, they speak of this thing called ‘knowledge’. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn56.18:1.3",
          "pli": "Katamā nu kho, bhante, vijjā; ",
          "en": "What is knowledge? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn56.18:1.4",
          "pli": "kittāvatā ca vijjāgato hotī”ti? ",
          "en": "And how is a knowledgeable person defined?” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn56.18:1.5",
          "pli": "“Yaṃ kho, bhikkhu, dukkhe ñāṇaṃ, dukkhasamudaye ñāṇaṃ, dukkhanirodhe ñāṇaṃ, dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya ñāṇaṃ—",
          "en": "“Knowing about suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn56.18:1.6",
          "pli": "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhu, vijjā; ",
          "en": "This is called knowledge. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn56.18:1.7",
          "pli": "ettāvatā ca vijjāgato hotīti. ",
          "en": "And this is how a knowledgeable person is defined. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn56.18:2.1",
          "pli": "Tasmātiha, bhikkhu, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti. ",
          "en": "That’s why you should practice meditation …” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn56.18:2.2",
          "pli": "Aṭṭhamaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
